                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1764570851",
                        "id": "18153921706414191",
                        "text": "You will regret skipping this place if you\u2019re looking for cool, made-in-Japan souvenirs.\n\nWe\u2019re here at BEAMS JAPAN, located in Shinjuku.\nThis six floors store brings together everything made in Japan. From clothing and crafts to art and so much more.\n\nFrom sushi-themed cups to Mount Fuji\u2013inspired ceramics, from traditional Japanese cushions to unique daruma dolls, you\u2019ll find tons of cute and well-designed items.\n\nOn-the-second floor, you\u2019ll find Japanese pop-culture goods\u2014everything from comically designed T-shirts to items inspired by classic video games. Some pieces are created by local artists, making them things you won\u2019t easily find anywhere else.\n\nYou can also find practical items, like mini keychain purses and wristwatches with kanji on the dial instead of regular numbers.\n\nOn the other floors, you\u2019ll find home and lifestyle items, such as small interior goods and kitchen-related products. They also carry traditional craft pieces like sake cups and seasonal decorations.\n\nTheir main store is actually a clothing select shop, and of course you can buy clothes here as well. If you\u2019re interested in Japanese fashion, definitely check it out too!\n\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2702\ufe0e\ufe0e\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\nWe are now giving out our Tokyo guides for free!\nPlease follow and comment \u201cGUIDES\u201d, and we\u2019ll DM them to you!"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
